\f1\fs24 \cf0 mchelper is an application that makes it easy to upload new code to the MAKE Controller Kit, get info about it, send manual messages to it, and connect to it from Flash (or any other XML client).\
\

\b\fs28 Installing
\b0\fs24 \
Simply drag mchelper.app into your Applications directory, or anywhere else you'd like to keep it.\
\
On OS X 10.5 (Leopard), there has been a change to the way uploading works.  In order to upload new firmware to your board successfully, run the 
\b OSXUploader
\b0  installer included in this package.  This only needs to be run once, and will configure your system to allow firmware uploads.\
\

\b\fs28 Uploading
\b0\fs24 \
To upload new code to your Make Controller, you'll need to download a 
\b .bin 
\b0 file from www.makingthings.com/resources/downloads, or write and compile one yourself.  The default firmware is a file called 
\b heavy.bin
\b0 .  \
